The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 December is 10,950 (1,267.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 December, there were 906 new confirmed cases (104.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 December, there were 528 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 72% (378 extra cases).
